title: Source: Popovich out of hospital after incident
description: Spurs coach Gregg Popovich was taken to a hospital after an incident at a restaurant Tuesday but is now home and doing fine, a source confirmed to ESPN.
author: Michael C. Wright

title: O'Sullivan to overcome 'stage fright' to face Carter at Crucible
description: Seven-time winner Ronnie O'Sullivan says he will overcome "stage fright" to take on Ali Carter in the first round of the World Snooker Championship.

title: Norris 'on the right track' in Saudi practice
description: Yuki Tsunoda crashes in second practice at the Saudi Arabian Grand Prix as Lando Norris sets the pace for McLaren.

title: Norris fastest as Tsunoda crashes in Saudi practice
description: Lando Norris was fastest from McLaren team-mate Oscar Pisatri as Red Bull's Yuki Tsunoda crashed in second practice at the Saudi Arabian Grand Prix.

title: Amorim invokes spirit of 1999: At Man Utd it is never over
description: Ruben Amorim says he never lost hope in a Manchester United comeback against Lyon after being inspired by watching back footage of the famous 1999 Champions League final win ahead of the Europa League quarter-final second leg.

title: 2025 PFL 3 video: Dalton Rosta submits Sadibou Sy, hits 'Stone Cold' celebration
description: Dalton Rosta impressed in his PFL debut and then paid tribute to a WWE legend.
